Key parameters of CCPD. aR of CH3NH3PbI3−xClx perovskite devices (blue line) and perovskite decorated by CsPbBr3 QDs devices (pink line). bD* as a function of illumination intensity Ee. 405-nm continuous laser was used in the test, applied voltage VDS = VGS = 1, and irradiance Ee = 0, 166, 335, 492, 648 mW/cm2where L is the channel length (0.1 mm), W is the channel width (2.5 mm), and Ip is the difference value between light photocurrent and dark photocurrent measured at VDS = 1 V in the output curve. The maximum R is calculated to be 0.39 A/W (in CCPD), obviously larger than that of 0.22 A/W (in CPD). The enhanced responsivity of CCPD is attributed to the CsPbBr3 QDs sensitizer with high light absorption and efficient carrier injection in the perovskite layer.

